<html>

<head>
<title>serre.htm</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFF00">
<p><a href="96zmi.htm"><img src="96logo.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=160 height=140></a></p>
<p><strong><img src="spkout.gif" align=bottom width=32 height=32>ABOUT THE SYMBOLISM OF SPECIAL DAYS</strong></p>
<p>I hate special days, because they are hypocritical, pathetic, fake, and politically and religiously 
correct. They lead you to feel good through good actions performed only one day of the year . Is 
that enough?</p>
<p>Let's look at this week: &quot;Mothers' Day.&quot; During the entire year we should be proud of our mothers 
for all their gifts, and particularly the first one: life. Every mother is a working mother! Most of the 
time they have three jobs: working, housekeeping, and raising children. They are so awesome that I 
do not want to support the business strategy, the marketing operation, in order to sell more during 
one day, to celebrate them. I want to celebrate my mother every day through my actions and her 
understanding, rather than by buying the first object I find on the &quot;Mothers' Day&quot; rack at the mall.</p>
<p>This is the same for Valentine's Day. Do you show your love to your partner or your friends only 
once a year? One friend told me, &quot;It is a reason to be more cheesy.&quot; First, I hate to be cheesy. 
Second, cheesiness, hearts, pink, flowers, and chocolates are just an image of love presented by 
the media as an ideal. They are superficial. Did you ever think about those persons who never 
receive anything on Valentine's Day? The modern tradition is to give condoms. It is the only day 
when it is possible to have easy access to them on a campus where there are no visible condom 
distributors.</p>
<p>This reflection leads me to the subject of &quot;AIDS Awareness week,&quot; when everybody is so proud to 
wear the little red ribbons in order to show publicly their support. In fact there still is huge 
discrimination against HIV-positive persons. Socially they are still considered dirty and sexually 
deviant. Consequently, &quot;AIDS Awareness week&quot; does not have any deep meaning when it is 
difficult to find free or cheap HIV tests, when condoms and sexuality are still taboo, and when there 
is no real dialogue about drug addiction relative to AIDS -- just hypocrisy.</p>
<p>I also hate the sparkling, &quot;moral&quot; television shows that try to show Hollywood and the spectators 
their good actions and get their charity money all at the same time. The sense of guilt is proportional 
to the amount of money we see on the board. At the end we know more about the donators than 
about the symptoms of the illness or about the research 's evolution.</p>
<p>Women's Day. I have a particular hate for this one. We are a majority treated as a minority. We 
are inferiorized every day by the inequality in jobs, wages, and society. We are satirized, raped, 
abused, objectified, insulted, and hurt in many ways. Twenty-two states do not recognize domestic 
rape as illegal. And one day the male society decides to think about us after it spits on us for the 
rest of the time. I spit on Women's day!</p>
<p>And the most universal special day is Earth Day. It is so good to think about ecology once in a 
while. Every day humans consider the earth as their property, forgetting the next generations. And 
on this day each of us will make good resolutions in buying recycling containers, organic food, 
ecologically this, ecological that. We should begin by consuming less, which is the first positive step 
for any life on the earth. Additionally, ecology is also political and social. It is so funny -- I am 
becoming cynical -- to hear a politician talking on this day while he is encouraging the production 
and dissemination of nuclear wastes.</p>
<p>I could have an infinite number of examples, but most important is to understand the logic of these 
special days. Since we do not think about our bad actions every day, we take a symbolical moment 
to expiate all the sins. We choose a symbolic moment to expiate them all and clean our soul at the 
same time. Do you want to gain your Heaven in this way? It is pathetic and fake. Be realistic with 
yourself and your bad soul. Symbolism is not enough.</p>
<hr>
<p><font size=3><strong>--Barbara Serr&eacute;</strong><br>
</font><a href="mailto:barbara@lglobal.com"><font size=3>barbara@lglobal.com</font></a></p>
<p><a href="96con.htm"><font size=3>Back to ZMI 1996 Contacts</font></a></p>
</body>

