<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Beyond Identity Politics</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><IMG SRC="header.gif" ALIGN="TOP">
<HR>
<H1><A NAME="Beyondidentitypolitics">Beyond Identity Politics</A>   
<IMG SRC="beyondid.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>
Emerging Social Justice Movements in Communities of Color</H2>
<H3>Edited by John Anner</H3>
<P>Beyond Identity Politics: Emerging Social Justice Movements in Communities
of Color provides a long-awaited roadmap to the grassroots social justice
movements of the 1990s and beyond. 
</P>
<P>Rapidly changing urban demographics, downsized government programs, and
economic globalization require new social justice strategies and new organizing
methods that go beyond identity politics. This anthology of new and previously
published essays describes how organizers are building sophisticated, successful
multiracial political organizations in low-income communities and communities of
color. With their vitality, complexity, and fluidity, these new political
formations are, in fact, transcending the politics of identity and redefining
the very meaning of the phrase of &quot;community organizing.&quot;
</P>
<P>Culled from Third Force magazine, which is &quot;charting a new course for
leftist journalism&quot; according to Utne Reader, Beyond Identity Politics
describes a strikingly diverse array of struggles: Korean workers fighting both
Korean business owners and anti-Asian prejudice, Latinos creatively organizing
communities on both sides of the border, a national campaign based in inner
cities combining police accountability with crime prevention, Native Americans
forming a powerful anti-toxics network, artists and community organizers joining
forces to stop violent images of Asian women, and much more.
</P>
<P>According to Third Force editor John Anner, the face of activism in the next
century will be more democratic, more gender-balanced, more gay-positive, more
multi-lingual and more multicultural--effectively fusing the politics of
interest with the politics of identity. In an era when the right wing seems to
be winning all battles, Beyond Identity Politics presents a critical inside look
at progressive victories.
</P>
<P><I>John Anner is editor of Third Force magazine.</I></P>
<P>$14.00 paper, $40.00 cloth</P>
<HR>
