<BODY><IMG SRC="header.gif" ALIGN="TOP">
<HR>
<H1>Complete Listing</H1>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="americanfuture">The American Future</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="tomhayden">Tom Hayden</A></I></P>
<P>In this stimulating and readable analysis of contemporary U.S. political and
economic problems, Hayden focuses on the failure of liberal and conservative
programs alike and on the need for economic democracy.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-029-3 $8.00 paper. 0-89608-030-7 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="darkages">The Dark Ages: Life in the United States 1945-1960</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="martyjezer">Marty Jezer</A></I></P>
<P>An engaging and accessibly written discussion of the roots of the civil
rights and peace movements, the counter-culture, and the New Left in the 1950s
and early 1960s. &quot;Carefully documents America's transformation from a
nation flush with New Deal optimism and victory over the Axis to a
self-lobotomized imperial fortress so twisted with fear of &quot;alien&quot;
ideologies that it nearly choked itself to spiritual death. &#133; In a
pathbreaking chapter on agriculture, Jezer illustrates the postwar decimation of
the family farm and the mass introduction of chemical pesticides and herbicides
which would soon lead to a global crisis. &#133; To his credit, he also shows
what was really alive back then, what gave birth to the liberating outburst of
the 1960s. &#133; Marty Jezer has tied those strains&#151;dark and light&#151;into
a highly readable volume.&quot; &#151;Harvey Wasserman</P>
<P><I>0-89608-127-3 $15.00 paper. 0-89608-128-1 $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Previewsandpremises">Previews and Promises</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Alvintoffler">Alvin Toffler</A></I></P>
<P>A highly personal look at jobs; identity; sex roles; information age
politics; hidden forces driving the economy; and the pitfalls and promises of
social change.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-210-5 $7.50 paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Squaredancing">Square Dancing in the Ice Age</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="abbiehoffman">Abbie Hoffman</A></I></P>
<P>A book from the U.S. underground, covering Abbie&#151;in disguise &#151;interviewing
people, touring the FBI building, and organizing a campaign to save the St.
Lawrence River. The articles are creative, funny, nervy, and (gasp) political.</P>
<P><I>
0-89608-194-x $8.00 paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Theyshouldhave">They Should Have Served That Cup of Coffee: Seven
Radicals Remembers the '60s</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Dickcluster">Dick Cluster, Ed.</A></I></P>
<P>A collection of engaging essays and interviews by activists in civil rights,
women's, anti-war, G.I. movements, the Black Panther Party, and the League of
Revolutionary Black Workers.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-082-x $14.00 paper. 0-89608-083-8 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Thestateofasianamerica">The State of Asian America: Activism and
Resistance in the 1990s</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Karinaguilar">Karin Aguilar-San Juan, ed.</A></I></P>
<P>These essays give voice to contemporary Asian-American activism, offering
thoughtful, radical analyses on a range of pressing issues. &quot;In addition to
academics, contributors include visual and performing artists, and community
activists and leaders. The resulting multiplicity of voices and perspectives are
bound together by a progressive political agenda. Many of the essays are fun,
exhilarating, and provocative as well as enlightening.&quot; &#151;Choice</P>
<P><I> 0-89608-476-0 $16.00 paper. 0-89608-477-9 $40.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="CIAoffcampus">CIA Off Campus: Building the Movement Against
Agency Recruitment and Research</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Amichenmills">Ami Chen Mills</A></I></P>
<P>&quot;Long overdue&#133; Rich in experiences of those who have already taken
action, CIA Off Campus will be invaluable for those who want to organize against
CIA recruiting now and in the future.&quot; &#151;Philip Agee</P>
<P><I>0-89608-403-5 $10.00 paper. 0-89608-404-3 $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Howharvardrules">How Harvard Rules: Reason in the Service of
Empire</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Jacktrumpbour">Jack Trumpbour, ed.</A></I></P>
<P>&quot;Trumpbour has collected a wealth of data and views on the most
powerful university in the United States. He has gathered disparate stories
relating to Harvard's role in the national security state, in the corporate
elite and in the upper-class culture during the nineteenth and twentieth
centuries. These stories are vital background for anyone organzing, learning or
teaching at Harvard, but they also have broader ramifications for the history of
bourgeois ideology and class cohesion in this country, the intellectual
foundations of racism and the treatment of women in prestigious institutions.&quot;&#151;The
Nation</P>
<P><I>0-89608-283-0 $16.00 paper. 0-89608-284-9 $40.00 cloth.</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Exit13">Exit 13: Oppression and Racism in Academia</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Montepiliawksy">Monte Piliawsky</A></I></P>
<P>This trenchant and eye-opening critique of the racism and academic
repression endemic to American univerisities includes five theoretical essays
and a case study based on the author's experiences as a political science
professor at the University of Southern Mississippi in the 1980s. It is a useful
point of departure for understanding today's debates over multiculturalism,
racism, and sexism in the academy. &quot;A polemical and penetrating indictment
of the current status and future direction of American education.&quot; &#151;Sothern
Exposure</P>
<P><I>0-89608-096-x $7.50 paper. 0-89608-097-8 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Newvoices">New Voices: Student Political Activism in the '80s and
'90s</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Tonyvellela">Tony Vellela</A></I></P>
<P>&quot;The author chronicles current campus protest activity, interviews
student leaders and profiles organizations to prove his finally undeniable point
that student activism in the '80s is a vital and influential national movement.
&#133; It is an impressive study and a piece of history in the making.&quot; &#151;Publishers
Weekly. &quot;[Includes discussion of] a wide spectrum of political activity,
with chapters on divestment from South Africa, Central America, CIA recruiting,
U.S. military presence on campuses, racism, poverty, feminism, gay and lesbian
rights, and student empowerment. Such a statement of action and truth offers a
sign of hope for things to come.&quot; &#151;Sojourners</P>
<P><I>0-89608-341-1 $12.00 paper. 0-89608-342-x $35.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Universitiesinthebusiness">Universities in the Business of
Repression: The Academic-Military-Industrial Complex and Central America</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Jonathanfeldman">Jonathan Feldman</A></I></P>
<P>This book is an essential guide for students and academics seeking to expose
university complicity with militarism and repression in the Third World.
Presents an activist strategy for selective divestment, modeled on the
experience of the campus-based anti-apartheid movement.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-354-3 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-355-1 $30.00 cloth </I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Beyondhypocrisy">Beyond Hypocrisy: Decoding the News in an Age of
Propaganda</A></H3>
<P><I>Edward S. Herman</I></P>
<P>This spirited book offers abundant examples of duplicitous terminology,
trenchant essays, satirical cartoons, and a cross-referenced doublespeak
dictionary for the 1990s. </P>
<P><I>0-89608-435-3 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-436-1 $35.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Creativedifferences">Creative Differences: Profiles of Hollywood
Dissidents</A></H3>
<P><I>David Talbot and Barbara Zheutlin</I></P>
<P>Examining the lives of 16 people working in the entertainment industry, the
authors review the limits of Hollywood and reveal a commercial environment that
destroys people's spirit and integrity.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-043-9 6.50 paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Lookingglassworld">Looking Glass World of Non-Fiction TV</A></H3>
<P><I>Elayne Rapping</I></P>
<P>&quot;Rapping's political and cultural analysis of the industry is
consistently on target, precise, and to the point.&quot; &#151;Cin&eacute;aste</P>
<P><I>0-89608-281-4 $9.00 paper. 0-89608-282-2 $25.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Networksofpower">Networks of Power: Corporate TV's Threat to
Democracy</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Dennismazzocco">Dennis W. Mazzocco</A></I></P>
<P>This book is a startling expos&eacute; of the increasing threat to free
speech and democratic government. A broadcast insider with twenty years of
working experience with the major networks, Mazzocco describes the ways that an
ever-expanding U.S.-based multinational media cartel veils the machinations of
the corporate state by dominating worldwide markets for TV, radio, newspapers,
books, movies, cable, recordings, and videos. Few individuals within the
corporate media have ever explained to their audiences the significance of
concentrated ownership. </P>
<P><I>0-89608-472-8 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-473-6 $30.00 cloth.</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Primetimeactivism">Prime Time Activism: Media Strategies for
Grassroots Activism</A></H3>
<P><I>Charlotte Ryan</I></P>
<P>Ryan's book helps activists mount effective media campaigns and fills the
void between conventional &quot;how-to&quot; manuals and the sweeping, and often
defeatist, media critiques provided by radical theorists. Several case studies
illustrate her proposed strategies and solutions. &quot;&#133;a thoughtful,
clear, sophisticated book full of valuable advice for activists. I know of
nothing else like it.&quot; &#151;Todd Gitlin</P>
<P><I>0-89608-401-9 $14.00 paper. 0-89608-402-7 $30.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Rockin'theboat">Rockin' the Boat: Mass Music and Mass Movements</A></H3>
<P><I>Reebee Garofalo, ed.</I></P>
<P>&quot;Rockin' the Boat is a critically important introduction to the global
patterns of music and politics emerging over the past twenty years. Popular and
academic readers alike will find a pleasurable breadth of information and
analysis.&quot; &#151;Johnny Clegg</P>
<P><I>0-89608-427-2 $16.00 paper. 0-89608-428-0 $40.00 cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Signed,sealeddelivered">Signed, Sealed, and Delivered: True Life
Stories of Women in Pop Music</A></H3>
<P><I>Sue Steward and Sheryl Garratt</I></P>
<P>A fascinating look at the women whose involvement in the pop music scene
ranges from those who make the music to those who package the records; from TV
performers to women in the pressing and packing factories; from women in the
1950s to today. Many photos.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-240-7 $8.00 paper. 0-89608-241-5 $25.00 cloth.</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Theatreforthe98">Theatre for the 98%</A></H3>
<P><I>Maxine Klein</I></P>
<P>An inspirational argument for people's theater. It is a source and resource
that provides ideology, history, scenarios, training, and populist treatment of
traditional plays.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-000-5 $10.00 paper. 0-89608-001-3 $25.00 cloth.</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Trumpettoarms">Trumpet to Arms: Alternative Media in America</A></H3>
<P><I>David Armstrong</I></P>
<P>Chronicles 200 years of U.S. publications, from Tom Paines' Common Sense to
I.F. Stone's Weekly, The Berkeley Barb, LA Free Press, Mother Jones, and New Age
Journal.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-193-1 $14.00 paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Break-ins,deaththreats">Break-ins, Death Threats, and the FBI:
The Covert War Against the Central America Movement</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="rossgelbspan">by Ross Gelbspan</A></I></P>
<P>The core of this book, written by a Pulitzer Prize winning investigative
journalist, documents the wide-ranging FBI assault on CISPES.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-412-4   $14.00   paper    0-89608-413-2    $30.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="COINTELPROpapers">COINTELPRO Papers:Documents from the FBI's
Secret Wars Against Dissent in the U.S.</A></H3>
<P><I>Ward Churchill</I></P>
<P>Hundreds of FBI documents reveal that the Black Panthers, the American
Indian Movement (AIM), and other domestic organizations have been victims of FBI
repression. &quot;The book contains over 70 pages of endnotes, many of which are
very substantive, as well as a 28 page bibliography, a large index, and a rich
and large sampling of documents. Readers will find the documentary exhibits and
the authors' analyses enlightening in terms of the political controversies that
surround the program and the issues of public disclosure, constitutional rights,
and political freedom vis &agrave; vis governmental surveillance. A useful
contribution to numerous areas of interest&#151;constitutional rights,
governmental secrecy, history, political science&#151;that can also be read by
general readers. &quot;     &#151;Choice</P>
<P><I>0-89608-359-4   $16.00   paper   0-89608-360-8    $40.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Freedomunderfire">Freedom Under Fire: U.S. Civil  Liberties in
Times of War</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Michaellinfield">Michael Linfield. </A>Introduction by Ramsey
Clark</I></P>
<P>&quot;The great wars we have fought for the sake of liberty have been
accompanied, without exception, by the most draconian assaults on individual
rights. This is the theme of Michael Linfield's Freedom Under Fire, and he
documents it with examples from every war since the American Revolution.&quot;  
   &#151;The Progressive &quot;Linfield's work is both provocative and scholarly
and deserves serious discussion in the media and the major journals of opinion.&quot;
     &#151;Small Press Magazine</P>
<P><I>0-89608-374-8   $14.00   paper   0-89608-375-6    $40.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Warathome">War at Home: Covert Action Against U.S. Activists and
What We Can Do About It</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Brianglick">Brian Glick</A></I></P>
<P>&quot;You know your paranoid friends, the ones who don't discuss drugs on
the telephone and won't repeat the hottest rumors about fellow activists? Brian
Glick's smart, concise War at Home gives ample proof that these friends of yours
are not simply demonstrating their irrational fears. Nor are they suffering from
delusions of grandeur about their political work. &#133; Thankfully, though,
Glick does more than frighten us and run. Strategies for dealing with possibly
FBI-fabricated rumors, forged or anonymous letters, and suspected infiltrators
provide a sophisticated and even serene finale to his book. &#133; Commit all
his precautions to memory. Something tells me innumerable copies of Glick's
checklist will be needed before the approaching gay and/or angry 90s are over.&quot;
     &#151;Donna Minkowitz, Village Voice</P>
<P><I> 0-89608-349-7   $5.00   paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Confrontingenvironmentalracism">Confronting Environmental Racism:
Voices from the Grassroots</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Robertbullard">Robert D. Bullard</A></I></P>
<P>&quot;Finally a book written by and about people of color fighting America's
environmental racism! &quot;  &#151;Gail Small, Native Action</P>
<P><I> 0-89608-446-9   $16.00   paper   0-89608-447-7   $40.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Defendingtheearth">Defending the Earth: A Dialogue between Murray
Bookchin and Dave Foreman</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Stevechase">Steve Chase, Ed.</A> A Learning Alliance Book</I></P>
<P>&quot;This historic, touching and uniquely useful book&#133;presents
concisely and colloquially the current positions of two of the most courageous
ecological visionaries America has produced.&quot; &#151;Stephanie Mills</P>
<P><I>0-89608-382-9   $10.00   paper   0-89608-383-7    $25.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Dyingfromdioxin">Dying from Dioxin: A Citizen's Guide to
Reclaiming Our Health and Rebuilding Democracy</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Loismariegibbs">Lois Marie Gibbs </A>and the Citizens
Clearinghouse for Hazardous Waste</I></P>
<P>It's in our food. It's in our water. It's in our bodies. And it's making us
sick. According to recently released studies from the EPA, widespread exposure
to dioxin is destroying the health of the American people. In Dying from Dioxin,
Lois Marie Gibbs and grassroots activists at the Citizens Clearinghouse for
Hazardous Waste describe the alarming details of this public health crisis, and
explain how citizens can organize against this toxic threat.  Recognized as the
&quot;mother&quot; of the toxics movement, Lois Marie Gibbs lead the Love Canal
Homeowners Association in their successful fight to win relocation from their
dioxin-contaminated neighborhood. She is the director of Citizen's Clearinghouse
for Hazardous Wastes, a 13-year old environmental justice center working with a
network of over 7,000 local groups.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-525-2   $14.00   paper   0-89608-526-0   $30.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Fightingforhope">Fighting for Hope</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Petrakelly">Petra Kelly</A></I></P>
<P>An urgent call for a world free from violence between North and South, men
and women, ourselves and our environment.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-216-4   $7.00   paper</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Nonukes">No Nukes: Everyone's Guide to Nuclear Power</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Annagyorgy">Anna Gyorgy </A>and friends</I></P>
<P>A classic of its time. First published in 1979 just after the accident at
Three Mile Island nuclear power plant, this is a comprehensive and accessible
presentation of the ins-and-outs of nuclear power. It includes explanations of
nuclear plant operation, the fuel cycle, health and safety hazards, the
economics and politics of nuclear power, international anti-nuclear programs,
and alternative energy sources.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-006-4   $10.00   paper   0-89608-007-2    $40.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Thenewresourcewars">The New Resource Wars: Native and
Environmental Struggles Against Multinational Corporations</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Algedicks">Al Gedicks</A></I></P>
<P>Gedicks both paints a disturbing picture of the current situation and points
to hopeful signs of resistance and coalition that could successfully block
multinational corporations' resource colonization of native lands. </P>
<P><I>0-89608-462-0   $15.00    paper   0-89608-463-9   $35.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Remakingsociety">Remaking Society: Pathways to a Green Future</A></H3>
<P><I>Murray Bookchin</I></P>
<P>&quot;Environmentalism is no longer about wilderness protection: it's about
saving the collective neck of humanity. In this turbulent context, the questions
raised by Murray Bookchin, that annoying gnat[!], should not be ignored.&quot; &#151;New
York Times</P>
<P><I>0-89608-372-1   $10.00   paper   0-89608-373-x    $30.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Rethinkingecofeministpolitics">Rethinking Ecofeminist Politics</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Janetbiehl">Janet Biehl</A></I></P>
<P>&quot;Provides a sorely needed perspective on the relationship between
feminism and ecology, most significantly how both feminism and ecology suffer
when reason and critical social analysis are abandoned in favor of nature
mythology, goddess worship, and mysticism.&quot;      &#151;New Politics</P>
<P><I>0-89608-391-8   $14.00   paper   0-89608-392-6    $25.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Thesunbetrayed">The Sun Betrayed: A Report on the Corporate
Seizure of U.S. Solar Energy Development</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Rayreece">Ray Reece</A></I></P>
<P>A disturbing history of the collusion between federal and corporate energy
executives to control the development of solar energy.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-071-4   $7.50   paper   0-89608-072-2    $35.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="Economicreportofthepeople">Economic Report of the People</A></H3>
<P><I><A NAME="Centerforpopulareconomics">Center for Popular Economics</A></I></P>
<P>An alternative to the Economic Report of the President that explains how we
can achieve growth and democracy; why IMF policies make the Third World debt
problem worse; and how economic policies of the new right hurt blacks and women.</P>
<P><I>0-89608-315-2   $11.00   paper   0-89608-316-0    $30.00   cloth</I></P>
<HR>
<H3></H3>
