<head>
<title>ZMI Logistics</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body stylesrc="../zmag/frabout.htm">

<h1><img src="../gifs/titzmi.gif" alt="Z Magazine" align="top"
width="121" height="95">Logistics</h1>

<hr>

<h2>Where</h2>

<p>ZMI is held in Woods Hole Massachusetts. Students are housed
at a local Inn where we rent sufficient rooms. Classes are held
at a number of nearby sites. Dining is at the Swope Dining Hall,
which is part of the Marine Biology Laboratories. Courses are
held in a few sites, but mostly a large house-like structure
located on its own private beach. The whole site is on the water,
small town living. Natural, serene, a good balance for the hectic
pace of the program.</p>

<h2>When</h2>

<p>ZMI is held yearly in early June. In 1996 the session ran from
June 5 to June 14.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Fees</h2>

<p>The full fee for ZMI is $1,000 to cover room, board, classes,
computers, etc. Scholarships range from $250 to $500 but are in
short supply. The first payment each year is due March 1, to help
us reserve housing. All payments must be made by the sessions
opening.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Details and Applications</h2>

<p>Details and application forms appear in <em><strong>Z Magazine</strong></em>
each year, beginning in the December or January Issue. Since
there is much to fill out using a form from <em><strong>Z</strong></em>
is essential.</p>
</body>
</html>
