<body>
<p><a href="index.htm"><img src="../gifs/titzmi.gif" alt="Z Media Institute" align=bottom border=0 width=121 height=95></a> </p>
<h1>Related Books</h1>
<p><i>Through the Looking Glass -- Decoding Bias and Blather in the News</i>, Jeff Cohen and Norman Solomon, Common Courage Press</p>
<p><i>Inventing Reality</i>, Michael Parenti, St. Martins Press</p>
<p><i>Manufacturing Consent</i>, Noam Chomsky and Edward S. Herman, Pantheon</p>
<p><i>Unreliable Sources -- A Guide to Detecting Bias in News Media</i>, Norman Solomon and Martin A. Lee</p>
<p><i>The Media Monoply</i>, Ben Bagdikian, Beacon Press</p>
<p><i>Networks of Power -- Corporate TV's Threat to Democracy</i>, Dennis W. Mazzocco, South End Press</p>
<p><i>Corporate Control, Corporate Power</i>, Edward S. Herman, Cambridge University Press</p>
<p><i>Beyond Hypocrisy -- Decoding the News in an Age of Propaganda</i>, Edward S. Herman, South End Press</p>
<p><i>Prime Time Activism -- Media Strategies for Grassroots Organizations</i>. Charlotte Ryan, South End Press</p>
