<head>
<title>ShareWorld Game Page</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="images/blutxtr3.jpg" bgcolor="#A4B1B9">
<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Games</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld Games</h2>
<p>Shareworld creates online systems for organizations and their constituencies. The premium is on socially conscious online 
communication and activism, but having fun is part of creating community, so games are part of the show.</p>
<p>ShareWorld is a multi-media system. We have online teleconferencing in text, graphics, and audio. We also have facilities to help 
folks meet new people, find pen pals, and learn about one another. We are developing simulation facilities for political games and 
research, but we also have games like checkers, backgammon, more interactive ones, and chess, whose window we display here. </p>
<p>These can be played live, with both players on line and moving in turn. Or you can make a move, get off, and then next you come 
on if your opponent has moved you are so notified and you can make another move. </p>
<p>Here then is what the Windows version of the chess facility looks like:</p>
<p><img src="images/serv016.gif" align=bottom width=696 height=558></p>
<p>To find out more about our systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, please choose <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, 
here or above. There is extensive description and further links, but there are also numerous screen shots, and please be warned 
that these may take a little while to load...</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
