<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>LOL: About LOLU</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h1><img src="images/about.gif" alt="About " align=absbottom width=92 height=22> <a href="lolu/index.htm"><img src="images/hlolu.gif" alt="LOLU" align=bottom border=0 hspace=8 width=96 height=28></a> </h1>
<hr>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;</h3>
<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>Left On Line University aims to provide high quality courses across a range of disciplines 
and topics, inexpensively, and via telecommunications. In this way it provides access to 
quality faculty and classmates to people from all over the world. LOLU simultaneously raises 
consciousness and creates new ties among people who share the LOLU experience. </p>
<p>&nbsp;</h3>
<h2>Structure</h2>
<p>Each course runs for 10-12 weeks, the duration of each LOLU semester. </p>
<ul>
<li>Lecture courses involve weekly lectures posted by the faculty, and week-long 
discussions of the contents and derivative issues. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Reading courses function similarly, but with reading assignments rather than lectures as 
the basis of discussion. </li>
</ul>
<p>Decisions as to what course shall be given rest ultimate with the LOLU staff. But anyone can 
propose a course via the Table Of Contents option, <strong>Propose</strong>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</h3>
<h2>Courses</h2>
<p>Courses on LOL have two sources. First, they originate from solicitation by LOL staff or 
proposals made to LOL staff. These courses are LOL sponsored. </p>
<p>Another source for courses, however, is the broader ShareWorld System. Other organizations 
with online systems in the ShareWorld community, such as The Nation Magazine, or 
Greenpeace, etc., have their own online schools, as well. All courses sponsored by any 
ShareWorld System Sponsor are made available in all the schools. </p>
<p>LOL-sponsored courses may have students, therefore, from other ShareWorld Systems, and 
LOL students can take courses in LOLU that originate not only in LOL, but also in other 
ShareWorld Systems.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</h3>
<h2>Finances</h2>
<p>The current fees for course are $75 to take a course, and $30 to audit. There are special 
considerations given to those who cannot afford the going rates, though, since these fees are 
already very low, only the most extreme circumstances lead to further reductions. Funds are 
divided among faculty, sponsoring organizations/systems, and the ShareWorld project, which 
maintains the whole school structure.</p>
</blockquote>
</body>

</html>
</DOC>
