<h1 align="center"><font color="#FF0000"><img
src="images/ccs5.jpg" align="bottom" width="293" height="157"></font></h1>

<h1 align="center"><a name="top"><font color="#FF0000">Search</font></a><font
color="#FF0000"> Page</font></h1>

<hr size="3" width="75%">

<p><font color="#C0C0C0">Use the form below to search for
documents in this web containing specific words or combinations
of words. The text search engine will display a weighted list of
matching documents, with better matches shown first. Each list
item is a link to a matching document; if the document has a
title it will be shown, otherwise only the document's file name
is displayed. A brief </font><a href="#querylang"><font
color="#C0C0C0">explanation</font></a><font color="#C0C0C0"> of
the query language is available, along with examples.</font></p>
<!--webbot bot="Search" s-link
s-fields="TimeStamp,DocumentK,Weight" s-index="All"
s-dsn="default" tag="FORM" s-text="Search for:" i-size="40"
s-submit="Start Search" s-clear="Clear" startspan -->

<form action="_vti_bin/shtml.dll/search.htm" method="POST">
    <input type="hidden" name="VTI-GROUP" value="0"><p><b>Search
    for: </b><input type="text" name="search" size="40" value></p>
    <p><input type="submit" value="Start Search"><input
    type="reset" value="Clear"></p>
</form>
<!--webbot bot="Search" endspan i-checksum="34894" -->

<hr size="3" width="75%">

<h2><a name="querylang"><font color="#00FF00">Query Language</font></a></h2>

<p><font color="#C0C0C0">The text search engine allows queries to
be formed from arbitrary Boolean expressions containing the
keywords</font> <font color="#00FFFF">AND, OR,</font><font
color="#0000FF"> </font><font color="#C0C0C0">and</font><font
color="#0000FF"> </font><font color="#00FFFF">NOT</font><font
color="#C0C0C0">, and grouped with parentheses. For example:</font></p>

<blockquote>
    <dl>
        <dt><font color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>information
            retrieval</tt></strong></font></dt>
        <dd>finds documents containing '<font color="#FFFF00">information</font>'
            or '<font color="#FFFF00">retrieval</font>'<br>
            <br>
        </dd>
        <dt><font color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>information </tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FFFFFF"><strong><tt>or</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FF0000"><strong><tt> retrieval</tt></strong></font></dt>
        <dd>same as above<br>
            <br>
        </dd>
        <dt><font color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>information</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#0000FF"><strong><tt> </tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FFFFFF"><strong><tt>and</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#0000FF"><strong><tt> </tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>retrieval</tt></strong></font></dt>
        <dd>finds documents containing both '<font
            color="#FFFF00">information</font><font
            color="#C0C0C0">' and</font><font color="#FFFF00"> </font><font
            color="#C0C0C0">'</font><font color="#FFFF00">retrieval</font>'<br>
            <br>
        </dd>
        <dt><font color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>information</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#0000FF"><strong><tt> </tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FFFFFF"><strong><tt>not</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FF0000"><strong><tt> retrieval</tt></strong></font></dt>
        <dd>finds documents containing '<font color="#FFFF00">information</font>'
            but not '<font color="#FFFF00">retrieval</font>'<br>
            <br>
        </dd>
        <dt><font color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>(information </tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FFFFFF"><strong><tt>not</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FF0000"><strong><tt> retrieval) </tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FFFFFF"><strong><tt>and</tt></strong></font><font
            color="#FF0000"><strong><tt> WAIS</tt></strong></font></dt>
        <dd>finds documents containing '<font color="#FFFF00">WAIS</font>',
            plus '<font color="#FFFF00">information</font>' but
            not '<font color="#FFFF00">retrieval</font>'<br>
            <br>
        </dd>
        <dt><font color="#FF0000"><strong><tt>web*</tt></strong></font></dt>
        <dd>finds documents containing words starting with '<font
            color="#FFFF00">web</font>'<br>
            <br>
        </dd>
    </dl>
</blockquote>

