<html>
<head>
<title>ZMI Logistics</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#EEFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055"
alink="#FF3300">
<h1><img src="images/titzmi.gif" alt="Z Magazine" align="top"
width="121" height="95">Logistics</h1>
<h2>Where</h2>
<p>ZMI is held in Wood Hole Massachusetts. Students are housed at
a local Inn where we rent sufficient rooms. Classes are held at a
number of nearby sites. Dining is at the Swope Dining Hall, which
is part of the Marine Biology Laboratories. The site is on the
water, small town living. Natural, serene, a good balance for the
hectic pace of the program.</p>
<h2>When</h2>
<p>ZMI is held yearly in June. In 1996 the session will run from
June 5 to June 14.</p>
<hr>
<h2>Fees</h2>
<p>The full fee for ZMI is $1,000 to cover room, board, classes,
computers, etc. Scholarships range from $250 to $500 but are in
short supply. The first payment each year is due March 1, to help
us reserve housing. All payments must be made by the sessions
opening.</p>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
