<body background="images/blutxtr3.jpg" bgcolor="#A4B1B9">
<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Forums</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld Forums</h2>
<p>One of the most important features of any ShareWorld on line system is its forum facility. This allows users to engage in on-going 
discussions with one another, and sometimes with experts in a field. It promotes exchange of ideas and vision, but it also allows 
people to explore new ideas and develop shared agendas. </p>
<p>Each ShareWorld system has its own set of forums created by its membership and sponsoring organization. Some of these will be 
private to the one system's direct users, or even to just the staff of the sponsoring organization, in some cases. But many will also 
be made public to the whole community of ShareWorld systems. Thus, on each system, you can access forums created within your 
system, in all other ShareWorld systems, and UseNet Groups from the broader world of the internet.</p>
<p>Here, then, are some of the relevant windows from the Forum Facility. First, the message center window, also used for E-Mail, 
here shown with some message headers from a particular forum:</p>
<p><img src="images/SWforu4.gif" align=bottom width=636 height=392></p>
<p>Here are a couple of windows used to set your preferences for forums to track for offline reading and writing:</p>
<p><img src="images/SWforu5.gif" align=bottom width=521 height=270></p>
<p><img src="images/SWforu6.gif" align=bottom width=590 height=350></p>
<p>Writing and reading messages is analogous to what one does in E-Mail and includes formating, spell checking, file cabinets, etc. 
There is also a nice Web Related feature. If there is a web site address in a message, in a forum or in E-Mail, it shows up 
underlined and functions as a link. Click it, and your browser goes to the indicated site. Here is a window for reading messages...</p>
<p><img src="images/SWforu7.gif" align=bottom width=717 height=593></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>To find out more about our systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, please choose <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, 
here or above. There is extensive description and further links, but there are also numerous screen shots, and please be warned 
that these may take a little while to load...</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
