<html>

<head>
<title>ShareWorld Money Page</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="images/blutxtr3.jpg" bgcolor="#A4B1B9">
<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Economy</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld Rates</h2>
<p>So what does it costs an end user to benefit from a ShareWorld System? Well, there are two ways to join 
any ShareWorld based system such as Nation On Line, Wilderness On Line, Left On Line, and so on.</p>
<p>One can become a Basic Member, or one can become a Sustaining Member.</p>
<p>A Basic Member pays $10 a month. Basic Members can telnet into or make long distance calls into their 
on line system for unlimited hours for the one fee. They can also call local numbers we provide 
throughout the country to connect. For this type connection, however, their membership only entitles them 
to two free hours per month. After that they must pay the hourly rate for use (currently $1.50 soon to drop, 
ultimately to $1 an hour).</p>
<p>Sustaining Members can also long distance call or telnet into their ShareWorld System for unlimited 
hours for their monthly payment. For local calls, however, they get 8 free hours each month before they 
must begin to pay the hourly rate. However, in some parts of the country where we are able to establish 
speciall connection sites, Sustaining Members can call local access numbers and get online for unlimited 
hours each month for their single monthly fee.</p>
<p>Beyond connection the only additional costs on ShareWorld systems is for things you self consciously buy 
while online. These may include books you purchase, or magazine subscriptions, or fees for a course you 
take, etc. But there are No Hidden Fees at all no matter what you do.</p>
<h2><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </h2>
<p>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>ShareWorld Finances</h2>
<p>ShareWorld's costs are many and varied, as with any complex undertaking. The main components are 
maintain the hardware and developing the software for each new system, maintain and paying for phone 
links, developing content, moderating and handling system usage, legal, accounting, and other such 
matters, payroll, etc. </p>
<p>All income to ShareWorld is from the basic monthly fees and small add-ons to costs of courses, items 
bought on line, etc. When a user goes over the alloted two free hours a month of local call access (for a 
basic member) or eight free hours of local call access (for a sustaining member) the fees they pay beyond 
their monthly rate just cover the costs of providing them the extra local access. </p>
<p>Out of incoming monthly payments, on each ShareWorld System $2 per month per person goes back to the 
sponsoring organization for them to utilize in their own operations, however they see fit. sponsoring 
organizations also get revenues when people take courses they initiate, or buy products they put online, 
etc. As a result, ShareWorld Systems provide very substantial financial assistance to diverse progressive 
organizations, one of the most important things about our effort..</p>
<h2><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </h2>
<p>To find out more about our systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, 
please choose <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, here or above. </p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
