Quarterly is a publication devoted to human rights and uncovering covert
activity. </a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr><b><i><a href="http://www.essential.org/CMEP/">Critical Mass Energy
Project </a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.essential.org/CMEP/">Promotes
energy conservation and tracks government activities related to such issues
as nuclear power, radioactive waste, renewable energy and fuel efficiency.
</a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr></dt>

<dt><b><i><a href="http://www.doonesbury.com/">The Doonesbury Electronic
Town Hall </a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.doonesbury.com/">Doonesbury,
the witty and poignant cartoon by Gary Trudeau, has arrived on the Web
and it has a mission. In addition to daily political information, flashbacks
to historic news and Doonesbury cartoons, the site hosts a section called
Get Involved which encourages you to do just that. </a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr></dt>

<dt><b><i><a href="http://www.earthisland.org/">Earth Island Institute
</a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.earthisland.org/">Run by feisty
environmentalists, Earth Island Institute has a site which includes full-text
newsletters, and information on thirty projects related to everything from
from dolphin, whales and sea turtles to environmental justice to rethinking
paper. </a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr></dt>

<dt><b><i><a href="http://www.eff.org/">Electronic Frontier Foundation
</a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.eff.org/">EFF is a leading
non-profit civil liberties organization working in the public interest
to protect privacy, free expression, and access to online resources and
information. </a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr></dt>

<dt><b><i><a href="http://www.envirolink.org/issues/esa/">Endangered Species
Act On-Line Resource Guide </a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.envirolink.org/issues/esa/">The
Endangered Species Act is a critical, controversial and confusing piece
of legislation that serves to prevent human actions from pushing animals
and plants into extinction. The on-line resource guide is a one-stop shop
for information about the Act, and it encourages you to play a part in
preventing the Act from following the route of the dodo and the passenger
pigeon. </a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr></dt>

<dt><b><i><a href="http://www.edf.org">Environmental Defense Fund </a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.edf.org">EDF is a non-profit
organization which aims to stop environmental pollution by encouraging
business, labor, government, and citizen groups to cooperate and identify
practical policies to protect the environment. </a></font></i></b></dd>

<dt>
<hr></dt>

<dt><b><i><a href="http://www.enviroindustry.com/">Environmental Industry
<font SIZE=-1>(Added: 3/7/96)</font> </a></i></b></dt>

<dd><b><i><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.enviroindustry.com/">This site
hosts information on businesses that provide environmental products and/or
services. It lists companies, organizations and publications. It also includes
a calendar of related events. </a></font></i></b></dd>

