<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Polls and Agenda</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld Polls and Agenda Setting</h2>
<p>Shareworld creates online systems for organizations and their constituencies. The premium is on socially conscious online 
communication and activism, and keeping track of people's viewpoints as well as setting agendas for system events and to convey 
information about events in society by an active calendar is part of ShareWorld's special functionality.</p>
<p>The Polling system allows for multiple choose, true false, yes know and fill in questions, and tracks results statistically for anyone 
interested to consult. These tools can be used to gauge views. or to take organizational or system votes.</p>
<p>Here, then, are a couple of the poll related views from a typical ShareWorld System:</p>
<p><img src="images/SWpoll1.gif" align=bottom width=488 height=325></p>
<blockquote>
<p><img src="images/SWpoll2.gif" align=bottom width=432 height=398></p>
</blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Another ShareWorld facility, on all our online systems, if our agenda tool. It lets users enter events and dates, and allows the 
system operators to do so as well. Users can be warned of upcoming events, events can have descriptions and reminders and 
links, and so on. Here is just the main &quot;find a date&quot; calendar window.</p>
<p><img src="images/serv015.gif" align=bottom width=643 height=418></p>
<p>To find out more about our systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, please choose <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, 
here or above. There is extensive description and further links, but there are also numerous screen shots, and please be warned 
that these may take a little while to load...</p>
