<H2><IMG SRC="..\gifs/blhelp.gif" ALT="ZNet HELP" ALIGN="TOP" HSPACE="4">
<IMG SRC="..\gifs/mdznet.gif" ALIGN="TOP" HSPACE="4">
<IMG SRC="..\gifs/lghelp.gif" ALIGN="TOP" VSPACE="12" HSPACE="4">
</H2> 
<CENTER>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P><A><IMG
SRC="..\gifs/smznet.gif" ALT="ZNet | " ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0" HSPACE="4">
</A>
<A HREF="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><IMG
SRC="..\gifs/feedback.gif" ALT="Feedback" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0" HSPACE="4">
</A>
</P>
<HR>    
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>If you are new to the World Wide Web (WWW), <STRONG>don't be intimidated!
</STRONG> Most browsers (the programs you use to navigate the Web) indicate that
an element of text is a
<STRONG>hyperlink</STRONG> by underlining it.  And most of the graphic elements
on this site (if your browser displays them) are also links. Graphical browsers,
like Mosaic and Netscape, allow you to follow links just by clicking on them
with the mouse.  Text based browsers, like Lynx, let you follow links through
various keyboard schemes; consult the help facilities of your browser.  When in
doubt, click!--the Web is robust: you can't hurt it. 
</P>
<P>
To use the World Wide Web effectively, unless you're already directly connected
to the Internet, you need a PPP/SLIP connection, available through
<A HREF="lbbs/index.htm">LBBS</A>. 
</P>
<P>
You'll also need a browser, program for viewing Web documents.
<STRONG>Netscape is recommended</STRONG> for the best viewing of this site, and
is available to
<A HREF="http://home.mcom.com/comprod/mirror/index.html">download</A> at no
charge from Netscape Communications Corporation, which is not affiliated with
ZNet or LBBS.
</P> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Starting Points</H3> 
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Here is a list of some links to WWW catalogs and other good starting points
for browsing.  
</P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Computers/Internet/Beginner_s_Guides/"><B>Internet
Beginner's Guides</B></A>  
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.lm.com/~lmann/docs/easymosaic.html"><B>Easy Mosaic
and Introductory Web Surfing</B></A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.sils.umich.edu/~fprefect/inet/using/html.html"><B>Starting
to use the Web</B></A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/General/Internet/WWW/HTMLPrimer.html"><B>

A Beginner's Guide to HTML</B></A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www-slis.lib.indiana.edu/Internet/programmer-page.html"><B>

A Primer for creating Web Resources</B></A> 
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://scholar.lib.vt.edu/reports/Servers-web.html"><B>Spinning
the Web: Setting Up World Wide Web Server</B></A> 
</LI> 
</UL>
<P><A><B>Yahoo</B></A> is the name of a service that provides excellent
guidance through the WWW, including useful listings, links, searh options, etc.
etc. Connect with them if you want to do some serious browsing or researching on
the World Wide Web. 
</P> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>
