<h1><img src="../gifs/titzmi.gif" alt="Z Magazine" align="top"
width="121" height="95"> Course Information</h1>

<p>ZMI offers courses in politics, media studies, computer
skills, and project skills, has project work groups, and evening
speakers. Here is a listing of some of our course offerings. Each
year the selection changes somewhat, but the total of courses
offered is usually around 75. The numbers indicate multi-level
courses such as Gender 1, Gender 2, and Gender 3, etc. Each
course runs for an hour and a half. Each day has four course
periods, though one of these is often given over to project group
meetings, and a special hour slot for student run courses,
special sessions, etc. Student run sessions are scheduled as we
proceed through the sessions. The list below changes somewhat,
yearly, depending on who is going to be available, etc.</p>

<hr>

<h1>Politics</h1>

<ul>
    <li>Gender 1-3 -- Sargent, Peters, Cerullo</li>
    <li>Queer Theory -- Cerullo, Bronski</li>
    <li>Race 1-3 -- Lusane, Daniels, Scott</li>
    <li>Black History 1-2 -- Daniels</li>
    <li>Political Economy 1-2 -- Albert, Bohmer</li>
    <li>Radical Theory 1-3 -- Albert</li>
    <li>Ecology 1-2 -- Hawkins, Tokar</li>
    <li>Foreign Policy 1-2 -- Shalom, Bohmer</li>
    <li>Economic Vision 1-3 -- Albert</li>
    <li>Revolutionary Strategy -- Staff</li>
    <li>State of the U.S. -- Chomsky</li>
    <li>War and Society -- Ehrenreich</li>
</ul>

<h1>Media Studies</h1>

<ul>
    <li>Mainstream Media 1-4 -- Barsamian, Sargent, Peters</li>
    <li>Strategies for Accessing Media 1-2 -- Ryan</li>
    <li>Alternative Media 1-2 -- Sargent, Peters</li>
    <li>Research and Investigation -- Sklar, Berlet</li>
    <li>The South End Press and Z Experiences -- Shah, Sargent</li>
    <li>Media and Political Satire -- Sargent</li>
</ul>

<h1>Computer Skills</h1>

<ul>
    <li>DOS and Windows Introduction -- Ascheim</li>
    <li>Word Processing 1-2 -- Ascheim</li>
    <li>Desktop Publishing 1-2 -- Ascheim, Peters</li>
    <li>Graphics 1-2 -- Ascheim</li>
    <li>Spreadsheets 1-2 -- Shah</li>
    <li>Database 1-2 -- Ascheim</li>
    <li>Telecommunications 1-3 -- Ascheim</li>
</ul>

<h1>Project Skills</h1>

<ul>
    <li>Production/print 1-2 -- Peters, Brooks</li>
    <li>Production/radio 1-2 -- Barsamian</li>
    <li>Production/organizing materials -- Shah</li>
    <li>Distribution and Promotion/print -- Brooks</li>
    <li>Distribution and Promotion/radio -- Barsamian</li>
    <li>Organizational Structure and Process 1-2 -- Albert,
        Sargent</li>
    <li>Fund raising -- Cagan, Albert</li>
    <li>Finances -- Shah</li>
    <li>Editorial -- San Juan, Brooks</li>
    <li>Editing -- San Juan</li>
    <li>Design/Layout -- Sargent</li>
</ul>

<h1>Project Groups</h1>

<ul>
    <li>Print 1-5 -- Albert, Brooks, Sargent</li>
    <li>Radio 1-5 -- Barsamian</li>
    <li>Organizing 1-5 -- Cagan, Scott</li>
    <li>Media Studies 1-5 -- Sargent, Peters</li>
    <li>Telecommunications 1-5 -- Ascheim</li>
</ul>

<h1>Evening Talks</h1>

<ul>
    <li>Noam Chomsky: Media and U.S. Policy</li>
    <li>Bell Hooks: Race, Gender, and Culture</li>
    <li>Barbara Ehrenreich: Trash Media</li>
    <li>Ron Daniels: Organizing, Race, and Media</li>
    <li>Michael Albert: Alternative Media, Prospect and Strategy</li>
    <li>Lydia Sargent: Feminism and Culture</li>
</ul>
</body>
