<h2>Sample Lectures<font size=3> </font></h2>
<p><font size=3>Each LOLU course meets for from 10 to 12 weeks. Each week the faculty posts a lecture, or a 
reading. During the week students ask questions, answer questions, offer comments, etc. And 
the faculty answer questions, promote dialogue, etc. It is rather like a typical university 
course in all respects.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>Here are three sample lectures you can look at. In a course, lectures appear in forums where 
it is easy to react, reply, query, etc., and for all to partake.</font></p>
<p>Michael Albert: <a href="lolu/alblect.htm"><b>What is an Economy</b>, etc.</a> </p>
<p>Juliet Schor: <a href="lolu/schorlec.htm"><b>More on &quot;Keeping Up With the Joneses&quot;</b></a> </p>
<dl>
<dt>Robin Hahnel: <a href="lolu/hahlec.htm"><b>Different Economic Visions</b></a> </dt>
<dd>&#160; </dd>
</dl>
</blockquote>
