    <h2>Lydia Sargent</h2>
    <p>Lydia Sargent is a founder and member of the staff of <em><strong>Z
    Magazine</strong></em><em>. </em>She also co-founded South
    End Press and the Z Media Institute, which she coordinates.</p>
    <p>Lydia's political roots go back to the anti-Vietnam War
    movement and her involvements have been varied since.</p>
    <p>Lydia is also a playwrite, director, and actor of many
    socially relevant plays, and has operated her own theatre
    group in Boston, and now in Woods Hole MA, including
    performing, directing, and writing. She writes a regular
    column, Hotel Satire, for Z.</p>
</blockquote>
