<html>

<head>
<title>LOLU: The Left On Line University</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#EEFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h2 align=center><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/lglolu.gif" alt="LOLU: The Left On Line University" align=bottom border=0 width=452 height=72></a></h2>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<p>The Left On Line University (another name for the ShareWorld Systems Ideas on Line University) 
provides three semesters per year of non-jargonistic, university level, fifteen-week courses 
accessible via the Left On Line communications system in political, social, economic, historical, and 
activist topics. Notable faculty have included Noam Chomsky, Howard Zinn, Juliet Schor, Michael 
Albert, Holly Sklar, Robin Hahnel, Steven Shalom, and others.</p>
<p>Courses will begin anew in the first week of October, 1996. To take courses you must join Left On 
Line.</p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="frabout.htm"><img src="../gifs/about.gif" alt="About LOLU" align=bottom border=0 width=92 height=22><img src="../gifs/blank.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=1 height=1><img src="../gifs/hlolu.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=96 height=28></a> </dt>
<dd>An overview of the LOLU's purpose and structure, how faculty are chosen, finances, etc. </dd>
