<body bgcolor="#C7C712">
<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Online 
Communities</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><img src="images/hservs.gif" alt="[Page Banner Image]" align=bottom width=471 height=49> </p>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p>Many of the pages in this site have large graphics to convey an image of what our online systems are 
all about. We apologize for the slow loading on some systems. </p>
<h1><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7></h1>
<p>&#160;</p>
<h1>What is a ShareWorld System?</h1>
<p>ShareWorld provides its clients on line systems for their members and staffs to access with either 
Netscape or Microsoft web browsers. We try to minimize graphical delays and maximize ease of 
use and functionality. We offer extensive content, community, and functionality.</p>
<p>A particularly nice thing about ShareWorld Systems is that you can join a ShareWorld System from 
online, even from a web browser, should you decide you wish to.</p>
<h2><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7></h2>
<h2>ShareWorld System Functionality</h2>
<p>Our online systems offer (or will soon offer) a host of different capabilities and options. These are 
available in somewhat different form and function for different platforms, but an indicative list must 
include:</p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>A congenial, civil, supportive community of users</li>
<li>Friendly, informed, tech support</li>
<li>Diverse offerings from the sponsoring organizations, such as The Nation, or 
The Wilderness Society, etc.</li>
<li>Full text search file libraries of diverse articles</li>
<li>Extensive guidance with Web Browsing, regularly updated</li>
<li>E-Mail far and wide, with formating, spell checking, and web links</li>
<li>Political and educational Forums often with noted activists and 
scholars--moderated, and without harassment, sexism, flaming, etc.</li>
<li>Online university and high school courses from fantastic faculty</li>
<li>Polls and agenda setting for organizational and other purposes</li>
<li>Book and Magazine Clubs</li>
<li>Teleconferencing with audio capability...(coming)</li>
<li>A Children's Center and Children&#146;s Internet help including the ability to limit 
web browsing access</li>
<li>Sensible adult socializing, an on line buddy system, and internet help for 
adults.</li>
<li>Activism on Line by fax and email</li>
<li>Job offerings on line where people can post and find listings</li>
<li>Alternative Radio (coming) </li>
<li>Issues and events announcements by system operators and users</li>
<li>Games like chess and checkers online that people can play simultaneously, or 
a move at a time like email</li>
<li>Audio calls without long distance fees&#133;(coming)</li>
<li>Offerings from the rest of the ShareWorld Community<br>
And much more&#133;.</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<table cellpadding=2 width=100%>
<tr><td width=50%><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7></td></tr>
</table>
</blockquote>
<p>&#160; </p>
<h2><a name="What the Client Gets">What the Sponsoring Client Organization Gets</a></h2>
<p>An organization that decides to establish on online system in partnership with ShareWorld, such as 
the Nation Magazine or the Wilderness Society, or another non-profit, periodical, union, or other 
constituency based organization, gets...</p>
<p>&#160;&#160;</p>
<h3>Key Benefits of ShareWorld Systems for clients compared to having only 
a robust web site:</h3>
<dl>
<dd><img src="images/bullet.gif" alt="[Bullet]" align=bottom width=14 height=14> Much greater functionality, allowing tighter ties with your constituency, greater gains from 
interactivity, etc.</dd>
<dd><img src="images/bullet.gif" alt="[Bullet]" align=bottom width=14 height=14> Increased identification and connection within your community</dd>
<dd><img src="images/bullet.gif" alt="[Bullet]" align=bottom width=14 height=14> A revenue stream to help finance your public site and your other projects, as well</dd>
</dl>
<h2><a name="Costs to Clients and Client Responsibilities">Costs to Clients and Client Responsibilities</a></h2>
<p>When an organization decides to contract for a ShareWorld online system it does take on some 
responsibility for the resuling facility. While ShareWorld provides all the technical tools and the 
maintanence, tech support, online and phone help, etc., and passes along revenues, the client has 
two primary responsibilities, and a variety of additional options.</p>
<p>First, the client has to agree to help ShareWorld promote the new system by (1) running ads or 
descriptive articles in client literature, (2) including reference to the system in client promotional 
mailings, and (3) providing ShareWorld the client's constituency list for both mailings and phone 
solicitation for the client's new online system. </p>
<p>And second, the client needs to oversee the design and definition of the system, being sure that it fits 
the client's needs and specifications and also to help provide content for the system particularly 
rooted in the client organization's services, agenda, and social involvements. </p>
<p>Beyond this, clients are also free to use ShareWorld Systems to create organizational tools for their 
staff's private use, to participate to greater extents in forums, courses, in other ShareWorld 
offerings, in providing information for the system, and so on.</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7></p>
<h2><a name="What the End User Gets">What the End User Gets</a></h2>
<p>&#160;Key Benefits of ShareWorld Systems for end users compared to joining AOL or Compuserve:</p>
<dl>
<dd><img src="images/bullet.gif" alt="[Bullet]" align=bottom width=14 height=14> Your money supports projects you believe in</dd>
<dd><img src="images/bullet.gif" alt="[Bullet]" align=bottom width=14 height=14> You benefit from a closed system, within still larger closed systems, creating a congenial 
and mutually supportive environment.</dd>
<dd><img src="images/bullet.gif" alt="[Bullet]" align=bottom width=14 height=14> You benefit from enhanced functionality and options, sophisticated and non commercial 
content...</dd>
<dd>&#160;</dd>
</dl>
