<body background="images/blutxtr3.jpg" bgcolor="#A4B1B9">
<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld Internet Options</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld Internet</h2>
<p>Of course all ShareWorld on line systems are tightly integrated with the whole internet. Users can easily 
browse the web, use telnet or ftp, and use more sophisticated tools as well. Users with internet accounts 
elsewhere that they wish to maintain can telnet into ShareWorld Systems. Other users can use their 
ShareWorld System account, with Left On Line, say, or Nation On Line, as their internet provider as well 
as for its own unique features. </p>
<p>Here, then, is the typical ShareWorld system menu for using the Internet... (We supply MS. Explorer on 
installation disks, because it is available free and with minor contractual terms. We also provide easy 
download and installation of Netscape, however.)</p>
<p><img src="images/serv014.gif" align=bottom width=513 height=486></p>
<p>And here is a second related window...</p>
<p><img src="images/SWinet8.gif" align=bottom width=544 height=486></p>
<p>Browsing is done with Microsoft Explorer, which ShareWorld provides, or Netscape, which our users 
can easily download. There is no installation complexity...it is all automatic.</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>What about A Web Site?</h2>
<p>ShareWorld's clients all have web sites, of course, and these both promote and also provide a jumping 
off access point to their more robust On Line Systems. </p>
<p>But even beyond this, users of ShareWorld created online systems have the option to create their own 
personal web sites and to maintain them through such systems -- Wilderness On Line, Nation on Line, Left 
on Line, and so on. Setting up and updating sites is easy, and the sites are housed in our large and very 
fast systems. This facet of our operations is under construction, but should be ready for use in a matter of 
weeks.</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<p>To find out more about our systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, 
please choose <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, here or above. There is extensive description and further links, but there are also 
numerous screen shots, and please be warned that these may take a little while to load...</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
