<h1><font color="#0000A0"><font size=7><em><strong>ShareWorld E-Mail</strong></em></font></font></h1>
<p><a href="swindex.htm"><img src="images/bhome.gif" alt="[Home Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=56 height=14></a><a href="news.htm"><img src="images/bnews.gif" alt="[What's New Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=58 height=14></a><a href="serv01.htm"><img src="images/bservs.gif" alt="[Products Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=57 height=14></a><a href="feedback.htm"><img src="images/bfeed.gif" alt="[Feedback Icon]" align=bottom border=0 width=59 height=14></a></p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
<h2>ShareWorld E-Mail</h2>
<p>E-Mail is arguably the most important single function on any telecommunications system. ShareWorld offers a number of 
approachs to E-Mail one of which we will describe here. It of course connects to everyone on a given ShareWorld system, such 
as Nation On Line, and to everyone in the whole community of ShareWorld systems, but it also connect seamlessly with all other 
internet addresses.</p>
<p>And the system is robust and functional, including the ability to format messages by font type, size, and color, paragraph and line 
settings, and so on. There is spell checking, file cabinets, etc. And, of course, there is excellent offline capability so that you never 
have to read or write while you are on the phone.</p>
<p>Here, then, are some of the relevant windows from the E-Mail facility. First, the message center window, also used for forums.</p>
<p><img src="images/SWemai1.gif" align=bottom width=636 height=274></p>
<p>Then we have the window that pops up to take addresses, etc.</p>
<p><img src="images/SWemai2.gif" align=bottom width=547 height=440></p>
<p>And the window where one writes a message...</p>
<p><img src="images/SWemai3.gif" align=bottom width=582 height=463></p>
<p>To find out more about our systems, their options and functionality, and how our clients and users benefit, please choose <a href="serv01.htm">services</a>, 
here or above. There is extensive description and further links, but there are also numerous screen shots, and please be warned 
that these may take a little while to load...</p>
<p><img src="images/div.gif" alt="[HRule Image]" align=bottom width=465 height=7> </p>
