<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Beyond Identity Politics</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><IMG SRC="header.gif" ALIGN="TOP">
<HR>
<H1><A NAME="Beyondidentitypolitics">Ecological Democracy</A>   
<IMG SRC="ecodcov.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></H1>
<HR>
<H3>By Roy Morrison</H3>
<P>&quot;This book is about building better lives, creating and nurturing
ecological communities; transforming the world...It is the adventure of family,
of pleasure, of rediscovering our lives. Come walk and climb and sit quietly
with me.&quot; -Roy Morrison, from the preface to Ecological Democracy</P>
<P>In this provocative, creative, and relevatory work, Roy Morrison explains in
practical and theoretical terms how to build an ecological democracy. Morrison's
heartening description of community-based democratic social practice offers a
realistic alternative to Newt Gingrich's right-wing nightmares and Bill
Clinton's neo-liberal dreams.</P>
<P>Offering a broad-based critique of industrialism, Morrison explores
currently emerging ecological democracies, such as the Mondragon Cooperative
system in Spain, the Seikatsu Cooperative Clubs in Japan, and Coop Atlantic in
Canada. He outlines a dramatically revitalized participatory democracy--which
includes community control of finances, a social wage, cooperative economies,
demilitarization, and a solar transition--and shows how to get there from here.</P>
<P>Written from the perspective of a longtime peace and antinuclear activist,
Ecological Democracy is an essential book not only for those concerned with
society's industrial crisis, but for those who want to build a just and
sustainable future.</P>
<P><I>Roy Morrison, a longtime peace and antinuclear activist, is the author
of We Build the Road as We Travel: Mondragon, A Cooperative Social System. He
lives in Warner, New Hampshire.</I></P>
<P>$16.00 paper, $40.00 cloth</P>
