<BODY><IMG SRC="header.gif" ALIGN="TOP">
<HR>
<H1>Writer's Guidelines</H1>
<P>We are currently seeking manuscripts that address:</P>
<MENU>
<LI>race, culture, and political activism</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>grassroots organizing</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>feminist theory</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>social movements</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>poverty, homelessness, and crime</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>disability</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>gay and lesbian politics</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>Asian American politics</LI></MENU>
<MENU>
<LI>third party politics</LI></MENU>
<P>We are particularly interested in manuscripts that are accessible to a wide
range of political activists, while being useful to an academic audience. All
submissions should include a cover letter explaining your proposed topic and its
relevance to our audience; a 2-page outline and summary of the book, or
alternatively, 1 or 2 sample chapters; a brief annotated list of the existing
literature on the topic and the niche your book would fill; any publishing
credits or activist or academic experience in the field.</P>
<P>
Please address all inquiries to Acquisitions, and include a large, stamped,
self-addressed envelope if you would like your materials returned to you.</P>
